This game is of right now off to a great start!

Pro's:
-Easy to control;
The game has easy mechanics that do hint at a possible console adaptation (or at least to the steam deck)
-The story is adorable and silly;
The Ellie and Virgil have a fun dynamic going on together that the people around them only fuel it more. Though, it isn't a story that should be taken serious the whole time. Still, a very good point in my opinion!
-The vibe of the game is calming;
A really laid back game that isn't asking you to be on the edge of your seat 24/7. A great time waster after a hard day of work. Or as a game to play while chatting with friends!
-Graphics are just right;
Nothing too much, nothing too little, I like it.

Cons:
-Has some rough edges;
Certain things like Text popping up when transitioning in a cutscene and being able to select everything at any time while walking around can be a bit confusing or frustrating.
-Performance is questionable;
Games like Stardew Valley are a lot more friendly on the FPS department. Not too bad, but it is a point that can be improved on for sure!
-Sidequests forced while playing main quest;
While working on your main quest it can sometimes push side quests onto you without really asking for them. In my opinion it would be better to keep it optional. Something I can live with, but expect to be getting these often.
-A slight edge of repetitiveness;
As of right now, it is mostly the same tasks you have to do to continue the game. While not really weird, I hope it gets expanded in some parts.

Overall this game is off to a great start. The cons are minor criticisms that to me are far from ruining this great experience. Definitely recommend this if you're into Animal Crossing or Stardew Valley!
